{"questionId":"816fedc1-1434-4eb8-aa3b-6715a1e738ae_22","correctAnswer":"-196","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Expand and use the vertex formula","content":"Expand: $f(x)=(2x-20)(2x+8)=4x^2-24x-160$. Vertex at $$x = -\\tfrac{-24}{2 \\cdot 4} = 3.$$"},{"title":"Substitute to find $f(3)$","content":"$$f(3) = 4(9) - 24(3) - 160 = 36 - 72 - 160 = -196.$$"},{"title":"State the minimum","content":"The minimum value is $-196$. The answer is <strong>-196</strong>."}]}